0: Don't be afraid to cry. It will free your mind of sorrowful thoughts.
1: Day and night cannot dwell together.
2: It is better to have less thunder in the mouth and more lightning in the hand.
3: They are not dead who live in the hearts they leave behind.
4: All plants are our brothers and sisters. They talk to us and if we listen, we can hear them.
5: Tell me and I'll forget. Show me, and I may not remember. Involve me, and I'll understand.
6: Before eating, always take time to thank the food.
7: When we show our respect for other living things, they respond with respect for us.
8: If we wonder often, the gift of knowledge will come.
9: Most of us do not look as handsome to others as we do to ourselves.
10: Those that lie down with dogs, get up with fleas.
11: In age, talk; in childhood, tears.
12: We always return to our first loves.
13: What is life? It is the flash of a firefly in the night. It is the breath of a buffalo in the wintertime
14: . It is the little shadow which runs across the grass and loses itself in the sunset.

17: Those who have one foot in the canoe, and one foot in the boat, are going to fall into the river.
18: The weakness of the enemy makes our strength.
19: When the white man discovered this country, Indians were running it. No taxes, no debt, women did all th
20: e work.  White man thought he could improve on a system like this.
21: A good soldier is a poor scout.
22: Poverty is a noose that strangles humility and breeds disrespect for God and man.
23: We will be known forever by the tracks we leave.
24: Do not judge your neighbor until you walk two moons in his moccasins.
25: There is nothing as eloquent as a rattlesnakes tail.
26: Force, no matter how concealed, begets resistance.
27: Our first teacher is our own heart.
28: Everyone who is successful must have dreamed of something.
29: All who have died are equal.
30: Remember that your children are not your own, but are lent to you by the Creator.
31: One rain does not make a crop.
32: Man's law changes with his understanding of man. Only the laws of the spirit remain always the same.
33: What the people believe is true.
34: You already possess everything necessary to become great.
35: There is no death, only a change of worlds.
36: Life is not separate from death. It only looks that way.
37: You can't wake a person who is pretending to be asleep.
38: It is less of a problem to be poor, than to be dishonest.
39: One finger cannot lift a pebble.
40: Beware of the man who does not talk, and the dog that does not bark.
41: All dreams spin out from the same web.
